				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E_{\text{Sun}} = W + Q,$$\end{document}where ESun is the input radiation energy from the sun, W and Q are the output work and heat energy, respectively. Accordingly, the equation of the heat flux can be expressed as Eq. 6:6SSun+SG=SW\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
