The aim of photon management in a solar cell is to increase the QEcell by minimizing reflection and parasitic optical losses. One way to increase QEcell is light trapping. In this case, the optical path length of light in the solar cell is increased by the design of the solar cell or a specific light trapping structure, which is integrated into the solar cell. However, the maximal optical path length enhancement is limited to 2n2, where n is the refractive index of the absorber material of the solar cell. Hence the quantum efficiency of a semiconducting slab is limited to (as Eq. 42)42QEcellE≅ACellE=1-exp-4×αE×n2E×d\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
